    "headline": "Eli Lilly (LLY) Is Up 6.0% After Obesity Data And Manufacturing Spend - Has The Bull Case Changed?",
    "summary": "Eli Lilly recently reported detailed late-phase trial results showing that people with obesity were able to maintain long-term weight loss after switching to oral Foundayo or lower-dose Zepbound, while also committing an additional US$4.50 billion to expand its Indiana manufacturing network for obesity and genetic medicines. The combination of durable weight maintenance data for Foundayo and Zepbound and large-scale production expansion underscores how central obesity treatments have become...",
